  To provide for those measures and actions necessary to minimize loss of operational capability, resources, and personnel during an emergency disaster or enemy attack situation.  To restore essential base
 and unit functions, relieve suffering, care for survivors, and to assist stricken civil communities when it is considered necessary and the capability and resources exist.
\par }\pard \qj\widctlpar\adjustright {\fs22\ul 
\par }{\fs22 5.  \tab }{\fs22\ul EXECUTION}{\fs22 :
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\fi360\widctlpar\adjustright {\fs22 a.  \tab 
The On-Scene Disaster Control Group (OSDCG), Disaster Preparedness Support Team (DPST), Control Centers, and Decontamination (Decon) Teams are staffed, trained, and equipped as outlined in Ellsworth AFB Instruction 32-4001.
\par 
\par b.  \tab Procedures for effective, 
timely notification and response in actual/potential emergencies or enemy attacks must be established.  This plan outlines the procedures necessary to respond effectively to major accidents, natural disasters, or enemy attacks while maintaining or minimiz
ing the loss of the unit operational capability.
\par }\pard \qj\widctlpar\adjustright {\fs22 
\par }\pard \qj\fi360\widctlpar\adjustright {\fs22 c.  \tab Air Force personnel will not be used to enforce or execute civil law in violation of Title 18, United States Code, Section 1385, the Posse Comitatus Act, except otherwise provided by law.
